<HEAD>Environmentalists Stage Protest Inside East German Border</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOF, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A dozen environmentalists protesting East bloc air pollution erected two tents on the East German side of the border as Communist border guards watched without intervening, West German police said. Police said the activists staged the protest Wednesday just inside <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> near where <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Czechoslovakia </LOCATION> meet. The environmentalists contend East German and Czechoslovak authorities are too lax in enforcing air pollution laws, resulting in harmful emissions that affect air quality in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> as well. Twelve of them erected two tents just inside the East German frontier, but outside the fence that separates the two countries. They also released balloons with slogans such as `` Pollution knows no borders.'' West German police said East German border guards watched the developments from a distance, but did not intervene. Czechoslovak sentries also watched from their side of the border. Five other environmentalists stayed on West German territory as the protest continued late Wednesday.
</TEXT>
