 Bush </PERSON>'s support of the program encouraging but said it is `` shameful that the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration forced a protracted court battle before obeying a congressional mandate.'' Of the 126 facilities found unsuitable because they lack sound floors, foundations, roofs, walls, electric power or sanitary or water facilities, 53 are buildings and 73 are land sites. The locations of unused or underutilized federally owned buildings listed as suitable for overnight shelters were listed as: <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION>, Point Arena, <PERSON> Tracy </PERSON> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Waycross </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ga. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Oxford </LOCATION> and Shoshone, <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>; <PERSON> Dana </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Ind </LOCATION>.; <LOCATION> Boothville </LOCATION>, La.; <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>, Md.; <LOCATION> Pontiac </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>; <PERSON> Remer </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Minn. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Vicksburg </LOCATION>, Miss.; <LOCATION> Tonopah </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Nev. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Binghamton </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Smithfield </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION>; <PERSON> Hauser </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Klamath </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Falls </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ore. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Phoenixville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pa. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Aquadilla </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Juan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Puerto </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rico </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Maryville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Carrizo </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Springs </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Rockwall </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tex