<BYLINE>By ALAN COOPERMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 250-foot cargo ship with 11 people sank in rough seas off the <LOCATION> mid-Atlantic </LOCATION> coast late Wednesday, leaving at least one person missing after he slipped through his life jacket during a rescue, authorities said. A merchant ship rescued two other crew members, the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> said early Thursday. After searching the <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> for two hours, a <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> jet spotted a life raft with an unknown number of survivors. A helicopter was dispatched to assist, said <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> Petty Officer <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> Arbogast </PERSON>. `` There were people on the raft waving flashlights, but we do n't know how many,'' he said The crew of the <ORGANIZATION> Lloyd </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bermuda </ORGANIZATION> abandoned ship in two rafts about 7 p.m. when the ship's load shifted, causing the vessel to sink about 160 miles south of <LOCATION> Nantucket </LOCATION> and 200 miles off <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> Lt. j.g. <PERSON> Jonathan </PERSON> <PERSON> Trumble </PERSON>. Searchers were hampered by 40 - to 45-mph winds and 20 - to 25-foot Despite the heavy seas and poor visibility, <PERSON> Arbogast </PERSON> said the crew's chances of survival were good. A merchant vessel, the Eagle, which was nearest to the <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Bermuda </PERSON> when the ship went down, was guided to one of the rafts by a <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> plane, said <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> Lt. <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Wolf </PERSON>. Two <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Bermuda </PERSON> crew members were pulled aboard the Eagle,