o days of demonstrations in the capital. Thousands remained on the streets Wednesday night. One group, as it passed the Ministry of Information, shouted: `` The head of the prime minister is a public demand!'' Similar unrest in March 1985 ended the 16-year authoritarian rule of President <PERSON> Gaafar </PERSON> <PERSON> Nimeiri </PERSON>. His defense minister led a coup in early April that began a process leading to the return of civilian rule a year later.
