<HEAD>Armenian Officials Cool to Sakharov Mediation in Ethnic Dispute</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ANDREW KATELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A top Armenian official on Thursday dismissed the mediation effort by human rights activist <PERSON> Andrei </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sakharov </PERSON> in the bloody <LOCATION> Caucasus </LOCATION> ethnic dispute, saying authorities can settle the matter on their own. `` I think we have sufficient help and advice from the government and party on the <LOCATION> Karabakh </LOCATION> issue,'' said <PERSON> Vardges </PERSON> <PERSON> Artsruny </PERSON>, a deputy premier of the Armenian republic, when asked if officials welcomed <PERSON> Sakharov </PERSON>'s mission. <PERSON> Sakharov </PERSON>, a 67-year-old physicist and Nobel Peace Prize winner, returned Monday from a trip to <LOCATION> Armenia </LOCATION> and the neighboring republic with which it is feuding, <LOCATION> Azerbaijan </LOCATION>. Armenians familiar with the mission said it was aimed at seeking a compromise in the 10-month-old rift over control of <LOCATION> Nagorno-Karabakh </LOCATION>. Armenians began strikes and demonstrations in February to press their demand that the territory, part of <LOCATION> Azerbaijan </LOCATION> since 1923, be incorporated into the Armenian republic. Azerbaijanis have refused to cede the district, and <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> authorities have sided with them. Clashes between Armenians and Azerbaijanis over the dispute have left at least 60 people dead. <PERSON> Bonner </PERSON>, who accompanied <PERSON> Sakharov </PERSON> on the trip with three other people she declined to identify, said President <PERSON> Mikhail </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> and his closest ally, <PERSON> Alexander </PERSON> <PERSON> Yakovlev </PERSON>, a member of the ruling Politburo, had approved the trip. She said the group visited the Armenian capital of <LOCATION> Yerevan </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> Azerbaijani </LOCATION> capital of <LOCATION> Baku </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Stepanakert </LOCATION>, the main city of <LOCATION> Nagorno-Karabakh </L