<FIRST>r a AM-Brites     12-29 0435</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Brites,0451</SECOND>
<HEAD>Brite &amp; Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAHOPAC, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 When it comes to pronouncing the name of this tiny community, the official ruling is hold the `` MAY-o.'' The <ORGANIZATION> Town </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Carmel </LOCATION> _ which includes the hamlet of <LOCATION> Mahopac </LOCATION> _ has ruled that the proper pronunciation is Mah-HO-pak, rather than MAY-o-pak. The vote Tuesday night was 3-2, reflecting the division on the long-debated issue in this community about 35 miles north of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Carmel </LOCATION> Supervisor <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Othmer </PERSON> said that in his experience _ which includes going door-to-door in the past 10 elections _ half the residents call the community Mah-HO-pak and half said MAY-o-pak. Surveys conducted in 1986 came to opposite conclusions _ one found 74 percent saying MAY-o-pac, and another found <ORGANIZATION> Mah-HO-pac </ORGANIZATION> preferred 113 to 23. The name is believed to stem from an American Indian word, but its original pronunciation is lost in history. <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Jewell </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Carmel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Historical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION> presented each board member at the meeting with a copy of the March 13, 1929, issue of the old <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mahopac </LOCATION> weekly, which bears the headline `` Mah-HO-pak is the Right Pronunciation.'' <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Carey </PERSON>, a lifelong <LOCATION> Mahopac </LOCATION> resident who is the town comptroller, seconded that pronunciation. He pointed out that the <LOCATION> Mahopac </LOCATION> high school song includes the phrase `` High above the Mah-HO-pak's waters.'' `` It's the out-of-towners _ those city folk _ who moved in over the years and changed the name of the community,'' he said.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>PASADENA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
