tration Wednesday when they found footprints leading across <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s southern border with <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>, said a military spokesman, who can not be identified by name under army rules. He said troops followed the tracks to a small truck south of the town of <LOCATION> Mitzpe </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ramon </LOCATION>, 10 miles from the border with <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>. The soldiers opened fire when the driver ignored an order to stop and killed three men. A fourth escaped, he said. Military helicopters circled above the <LOCATION> Negev </LOCATION> desert Thursday as searches for the missing man continued, <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> army radio said. State radio said the resort town of <LOCATION> Eilat </LOCATION>, 90 miles south of <LOCATION> Mitzpe </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ramon </LOCATION>, was cut off from the rest of the country for most of the day after the army closed the road for its searches. On Monday, Israeli troops killed three suspected Palestinian guerrillas not far from <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s northern border with <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. Three more guerrillas were killed in the same area on Wednesday. Also Monday, three guerrillas drowned when their boat capsized off the coast of southern <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> as they made their way to the northern Israeli coast. The army spokesman denied rumors that two <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> soldiers were injured in the gunfight.
