<HEAD>Yields on Four-Year Notes Hit 14-Month High</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Yields on four-year <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> notes rose in Thursday's auction to the highest level in 14 months. The average yield was 9.22 percent, up from 8.76 percent at the last auction on Sept. 28. It was the highest rate since four-year notes averaged 9.24 percent on Oct. 6, 1987. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 9 -LRB- percent with each $ 10,000 in face value selling for $ 9,968.90. A total of $ 7.26 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling $ 23.03 billion.
