<HEAD>Embassy Charges Terrorist Groups Learned From Arafat Organization</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BARRY SCHWEID</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Diplomatic Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Israeli government said Thursday that the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> set the examples for all terrorist groups which attack civilian airplanes and their passengers. A statement titled `` PLO: The first of its kind,'' did not directly link <PERSON> Yassar </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s group to the bombing of <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> Flight 103, the <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 747 jetliner that crashed last week in <LOCATION> Scotland </LOCATION> and killed all 259 aboard and an estimated 11 people on the ground. But the statement, released by the Israeli embassy, said all terrorist groups that have targeted civil aviation in recent years `` learned from one source _ the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>.'' <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s organization was the first to hijack an airplane, an <ORGANIZATION> El </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Al </ORGANIZATION> fight in 1968; the first to destroy a plane in midair, a <ORGANIZATION> Swissair </ORGANIZATION> flight to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> in 1970; and the first to carry out a gun-and-grenade attack on passengers, an <ORGANIZATION> El </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Al </ORGANIZATION> plane in <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION> in 1968, the statement said. `` Internationalist terrorist organizations have learned from the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> in other areas as well,'' the embassy said. It cited the murder of 11 Israeli athletes at the Olympics in <LOCATION> Munich </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, and the seizure of the Israeli embassy in <LOCATION> Bangkok </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Thailand </LOCATION>, also in 1972. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> investigators so far have been unable to pinpoint the person or group that placed a bomb aboard the <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> plane. At least two radical Palestinian organizations, both outside the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, are among a wide spectrum of possible suspects. These are The Popular Front for the <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Palestine-General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Command </ORGANIZATION>, and the <ORGANIZATION> Al </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fatah </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revolutionary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> headed by <PERSON> Abu </PERSON> <PERSON> Nidal </PERSON>. `` The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> has throughout the years develped links and cooperated, at times very closely, with other terror organizations,'' the Israeli statement said, `` providing them with funds, arms, training and operational assistance.'' In the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>, it said, <PERSON> Abu </PERSON> <PERSON> Nidal </PERSON> and others used terror methods which they first learned from the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> before breaking away to form their own groups. The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> itself `` has not ended its own campaign of terror, but has only redefined the direction, range and tactical form of the ` armed struggle,' which is another definition of terror and violence sanctioned by the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>,'' the statement said. `` From earlier years to more recent attacks, <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> violence shows that when it comes to terrorism, the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> wrote the book.'' Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> accused the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> of terrorism last month as he denied <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> a visa to speak to the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. He called the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> chairman an `` accessory'' to terrorism. Subsequently, <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> said he renounced terrorism `` in all forms'' and <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> approved <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> talks with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, the first authorized by the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> in 13 years. The first session was held Dec. 16 in <LOCATION> Carthage </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tunisia </LOCATION>. Afterward, Assistant Secretary of State <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> and other senior <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration officials cautioned the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> the `` substantive dialogue'' would be terminated if acts of terrorism were traced to <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s organization. There have been no <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> accusations against the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> since.
