<BYLINE>By KATIA BLACKBURN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TACOMA, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Hollis </PERSON> <PERSON> Day </PERSON> gave his daughter an extra warm hug the last morning of her Christmas visit and told her he would watch her 2-year-old handicapped son, <PERSON> Dylan </PERSON>, while she packed for the trip home. The 75-year-old man then drove off with his only grandson, leaving a note that said only: `` Gramps and <PERSON> Dylan </PERSON> have gone bye-bye together.'' On Thursday, two days later, <PERSON> Hollis </PERSON> <PERSON> Day </PERSON> and his grandson were found shot to death in a locked vehicle on wooded, family-owned land 50 miles away, Sheriff <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Logan </PERSON> said. The gun was near the bodies. Both were shot in the head. `` At this point, the evidence appears consistent with a homicide-suicide theory,'' <PERSON> Logan </PERSON> said. Autopsies were scheduled for Friday. <PERSON> Debbie </PERSON> <PERSON> Day </PERSON> said she had realized a few hours after her father left with <PERSON> Dylan </PERSON> that he may have been saying goodbye forever. `` He told me what a wonderful girl and mother I was,'' she said of the exchange Tuesday. Ms. Day, 40, said she called police a few hours after her father left. `` It's hard to believe he would hurt anybody, much less his grandson, but he'd written me a number of letters, talking about dreams he'd had about flying with <PERSON> Dylan </PERSON> into the hereafter,'' Ms. Day said. `` He had a hard time with the fact the boy was such a burden to me. `` He was n't a burden to me because I love him, but he wanted me to be free of this responsibility, which was all-consuming.'' Day had tried to give his daughter some time off, most recently offering to hire a nurse or a nanny for the boy while she went on a Hawaiian vacation. <PERSON> Dylan </PERSON> was developmentally disabled, his mother said. He could n't walk or talk, and the right side of his body was limp because of palsy <PERSON> Hollis </PERSON> <PERSON> Day </PERSON> was scheduled for cat