<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is a chronology of the major events of 1988: JAN. 2 _ <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> sign landmark free-trade agreement. JAN. 7 _ Record snowfall in the <LOCATION> South </LOCATION>, record cold across <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> JAN. 28 _ Face-to-face negotiations begin between Contras and <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION>. Polygamist 13-day siege ends in <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>. JAN. 30 _ <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Redskins </ORGANIZATION> defeat <ORGANIZATION> Denver </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broncos </ORGANIZATION> 42-10 in Super Bowl. FEB. 3 _ Contra aid voted down by House. <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> confirmed as <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> justice. FEB. 8 _ <PERSON> Dole </PERSON> and <PERSON> Gephardt </PERSON> win <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION> caucuses. FEB. 13 _ Winter Olympics open in <LOCATION> Calgary </LOCATION>. FEB. 16 _ <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> and <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> win <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> primary. FEB. 17 _ Marine Lt. Col. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON> kidnapped in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. FEB. 21 _ <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Swaggart </PERSON> steps down from pulpit in sex scandal. FEB. 23 _ Nationalist protests begin in <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Armenia </LOCATION>. FEB. 25 _ <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s President <PERSON> Delvalle </PERSON> fails in attempt to fire armed forces chief <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, indicted on drug charges in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> MARCH 8 _ Super Tuesday: <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> wins 16 of 17 contests, Democratic results split. MARCH 16 _ <PERSON> Poindexter </PERSON>, <LOCATION> North </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Secord </PERSON>, <PERSON> Hakim </PERSON> indicted on conspiracy charges in Iran-Contra affair. MARCH 23 _ <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION>,