<HEAD>London Stocks Rise on Last Full Trading Day Of Year</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates throughout.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stocks rose Thursday, the last complete trading day of the year, helped by a firm opening on Wall Street and some last-minute bargain hunting by institutional investors. Analysts said <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> stocks still look relatively cheap against other markets and that buyers crept in to pick up some late purchases before yearend. <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> 100-share index closed up 15.7 points, or 0.88 percent, at 1803.4. The narrower <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> 30 share index was up 16.0 points at 1463.1. The Financial Times 500 share index was 1,013.49, up 9.14. Volume was a relatively healthy 377.3 million shares, compared with the 203.7 million shares which changed hands Wednesday.
