TION>. Sale of the Puerto Rican stations leaves only WPGH, and the company has reached an agreement in principle to sell that to <ORGANIZATION> Renaissance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION>, organized by investor <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Finkelstein </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Warburg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pincus </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Capital </ORGANIZATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> buyout is expected to be consummated in January, <PERSON> Lorimar </PERSON> said in a news release, apparently indicating sale of the <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> station will be completed by then. A call to Chris-Craft's <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> offices late Thursday was not returned.
