PICKS UP 10th graf pvs bgng, `In virtually'</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MARTIN CRUTSINGER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Federal regulators, working against a year-end tax deadline, announced the sale of 13 more insolvent savings and loan institutions in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> on Thursday. The latest deals brought to 197 the number of insolvent S & amp; Ls which have been dealt with by federal officials this year, a post-Depression record, far surpassing the 48 <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Ls closed in 1987. Officials predicted that they are sure to top the target of dealing with 200 failed S & amp; Ls this year before a midnight deadline Saturday, when tax breaks for the buyers of ailing <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Ls will be cut in half. The latest takeovers included the first purchase of <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> institutions by foreigners. A group of investors from <LOCATION> Taiwan </LOCATION> agreed to buy eight insolvent <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> institutions. The latest deals followed two of the largest bailouts of S & amp; Ls. The government announced Wednesday it was pledging assistance totaling $ 6.8 billion to the purchasers of a huge <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> institution and five of the most financially troubled <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> S & amp; Ls. The agreements Thursday were announced after the three-member <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> spent the day huddled behind closed doors reviewing offers. In one of the deals, eight insolvent <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Ls were sold to <ORGANIZATION> Pacific </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> USA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cor