<HEAD>Wheeling-Pitt Files Reorganization Plan</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: CORRECTS lede to show plan was submitted in Pittsburgh court</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Wheeling-Pittsburgh </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> says it has submitted its initial plan for reorganization to the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Court here. A broad outline of the plan, which had been circulated earlier to the media, said the reorganization would reduce the company's current common stockholders' ownership to 7 percent Both <ORGANIZATION> Wheeling-Pittsburgh </ORGANIZATION> and lawyers close to the reorganization, now nearly four years in progress, said the final plan would likely look much different than the one submitted Thursday. The initial plan is seen as a starting point for negotiations among the company's creditors, employee groups and stockholders.
