<NOTE>EDS: UPDATES with morning dollar close, comments</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> dollar inched up against the Japanese yen in morning trading in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> Friday, the last day of foreign exchange dealings for 1988. The dollar opened at 125.75 yen, down 0.28 yen from Thursday's close, but moved to 125.93 yen by the end of the morning session Dealers said the dollar weakened in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> following a similar trend on overseas markets Thursday, where the West German central bank intervened with dollar-selling to prop up the West German mark. A dealer with a major commercial bank in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> described currency trading as `` very thin'' ahead of a three-day New Year holiday starting Saturday. The <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> held its last session for the year on Wednesday and will reopen on Jan. 4.
